To install critic2, please follow the instructions in:

https://aoterodelaroza.github.io/critic2/installation/

Windows builds
--------------

* Cross-compilation from Linux with MinGW-w64 (packages
  gfortran-mingw-w64-x86-64 and g++-mingw-w64-x86-64 on Debian/Ubuntu):

    cmake -B build-win -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=cmake/toolchains/x86_64-w64-mingw32.cmake \
      -DUSE_EXTERNAL_LAPACK=OFF -DUSE_LIBXC=OFF -DUSE_READLINE=OFF \
      [-DENABLE_GUI=ON -DGLFW3_ROOT=<path to unpacked glfw-*.bin.WIN64>] \
      [-DCMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING_EMULATOR=wine]
    cmake --build build-win -j

  See the header of the toolchain file for all options.

* Native build in an MSYS2 shell (no toolchain file needed):

    cmake -B build -G "MSYS Makefiles" [-DENABLE_GUI=ON ...]
    cmake --build build -j

The regression tests are POSIX-only and are skipped on Windows.
